result:
Not safe as-is. `Promise.all` fires all SKU lookups concurrently — a cart with 25 items saturates the pool from a single request, and two concurrent orders with 10 items each will contend. Under load you'll see pool timeouts, not just slowness.

The old sequential loop was pool-safe by accident. The right shape is bounded concurrency:

```js
import pLimit from 'p-limit';
const limit = pLimit(5);
const results = await Promise.all(skus.map(sku => limit(() => lookup(sku))));
```

Pick the bound based on pool size ÷ expected concurrent request count, with headroom. With pool=20 and, say, ~4 concurrent order requests typical, 3–5 per request is reasonable.

Check whether your ORM/driver queues on pool exhaustion or throws — that determines whether the symptom would be latency or 500s.

